Sure, if you have money you can buy more elaborate experience and maybe even buy affection from some of the people in your life. But the truth is you can be just as happy sitting by a campfire with someone you love  as you can be sitting on a yacht. You don't need a lot of money to enjoy the beach or backyard with your friends. You don't need any money to snuggle a grandbaby or reminisce with an old friend. I don't think modern society should be criticized for being materialistic. It is embedded in our culture and we all go through phases and years of wanting better and bigger stuff. At some point, we get tired of working just to buy more stuff.  => I
